The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Nation at a Glance

 Millionaire count up 68% in 5 yrs

 New Delhi (PTI): The number of millionaires 

 in the country has increased by 67.6 per cent in the last 

 five years, the Lok Sabha was told on Wednesday. 

 Citing data available with the income-tax department, minister of state for planning M.V. Rajasekharan said the number of income-tax assessees with income of Rs 10 lakh and above was 91,877 in 2004-05 against 54,805 in 2000-01. 

 Referring to the World Banks World Development Indicators 2006, the minister said the proportion of people living on less than $1 per day has also declined to 34.7 per cent in 1999-2000, compared with 47 per cent in 1994. 

 Prabhakar in dowry case 

 New Delhi (PTI): A case of dowry harassment 

 has been registered against former cricketer Manoj Prabhakar, 

 more than four years after his estranged wife filed a complaint 

 against him.

 Sandhya had filed the complaint of harassment for dowry in 2002, more than 16 years after her marriage. The couple has a 17-year-old son.

 We are investigating the matter and are collecting facts, police said.

 According to the complaint, Prabhakar, who had blown the lid off the match-fixing scandal before getting embroiled in it, tortured Sandhya in collusion with one Fareen, who she claimed was an actress.

 Sandhya had also accused him of cheating her and illegally removing her from the post of co-director of the cosmetic company that the two had set up. 

 Bus mishap

 Jammu: Sixteen people were killed when 

 the bus in which they were travelling skidded off the road 

 and rolled into a gorge in Rajouri district on Wednesday.

 Eight persons died on the spot, while eight others died in hospital. Twenty-eight people were injured in the accident. 

 Online nikaah

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): Muslim clerics 

 here have solemnised the marriage of a girl with a US-based 

 groom through the Internet. The marriage of Tasnim Johra 

 and Raza Abbas was scheduled for Tuesday. But when Raza 

 failed to reach India, their parents decided to use the 

 Net for the nikaah.

 Student protest

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): Students of Meerut 

 University lobbed stones at buses and forced the closure 

 of colleges on Wednesday to press for a probe into the reported 

 marking of MA exam answer scripts by 10-year-old kids.

An 80-year-old woman from Pakistan, who recently 

 met her sons in a Punjab village for the first time since 

 Partition, has urged the government to let her live in India. 




